&lt;p&gt;The Correct Answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Timeless Texts and Universal Teachings&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;IGNCA to Host Symposium on Gita and Natyashastra&amp;rsquo;s UNESCO Recognition.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;344&quot; data-start=&quot;198&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;344&quot; data-start=&quot;200&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong data-end=&quot;258&quot; data-start=&quot;204&quot;&gt;Indira Gandhi National Centre for the Arts (IGNCA)&lt;/strong&gt; will host a &lt;strong data-end=&quot;301&quot; data-start=&quot;271&quot;&gt;two-day National Symposium&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;in &lt;strong data-end=&quot;341&quot; data-start=&quot;328&quot;&gt;New Delhi&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;528&quot; data-start=&quot;345&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;528&quot; data-start=&quot;347&quot;&gt;The symposium is titled:&lt;br data-end=&quot;374&quot; data-start=&quot;371&quot; /&gt;
	&lt;em data-end=&quot;526&quot; data-start=&quot;376&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;525&quot; data-start=&quot;377&quot;&gt;&amp;ldquo;Timeless Texts and Universal Teachings: Inscription of Bhagavad Gita and Natyashastra in the UNESCO Memory of the World International Register&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;670&quot; data-start=&quot;529&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;670&quot; data-start=&quot;531&quot;&gt;It commemorates the inclusion of the &lt;strong data-end=&quot;585&quot; data-start=&quot;568&quot;&gt;Bhagavad Gita&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong data-end=&quot;606&quot; data-start=&quot;590&quot;&gt;Natyashastra&lt;/strong&gt; in the &lt;strong data-end=&quot;667&quot; data-start=&quot;614&quot;&gt;UNESCO Memory of the World International Register&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;757&quot; data-start=&quot;671&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;757&quot; data-start=&quot;673&quot;&gt;The inclusion recognizes their &lt;strong data-end=&quot;727&quot; data-start=&quot;704&quot;&gt;global significance&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong data-end=&quot;754&quot; data-start=&quot;732&quot;&gt;enduring relevance&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;879&quot; data-start=&quot;758&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;879&quot; data-start=&quot;760&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;775&quot; data-start=&quot;760&quot;&gt;Chief Guest&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;strong data-end=&quot;810&quot; data-start=&quot;777&quot;&gt;Shri Gajendra Singh Shekhawat&lt;/strong&gt;, Hon&amp;rsquo;ble &lt;strong data-end=&quot;855&quot; data-start=&quot;820&quot;&gt;Minister of Culture and Tourism&lt;/strong&gt;, Government of India.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;986&quot; data-start=&quot;880&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;986&quot; data-start=&quot;882&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;897&quot; data-start=&quot;882&quot;&gt;Chairperson&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;strong data-end=&quot;923&quot; data-start=&quot;899&quot;&gt;Shri Ram Bahadur Rai&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong data-end=&quot;950&quot; data-start=&quot;925&quot;&gt;Padma Bhushan awardee&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong data-end=&quot;983&quot; data-start=&quot;955&quot;&gt;President of IGNCA Trust&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1209&quot; data-start=&quot;987&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;1012&quot; data-start=&quot;989&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;1009&quot; data-start=&quot;989&quot;&gt;Guests of Honour&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;ul data-end=&quot;1209&quot; data-start=&quot;1015&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1122&quot; data-start=&quot;1015&quot;&gt;
		&lt;p data-end=&quot;1122&quot; data-start=&quot;1017&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;1047&quot; data-start=&quot;1017&quot;&gt;Swami Gyananand Ji Maharaj&lt;/strong&gt;, Founder of &lt;strong data-end=&quot;1077&quot; data-start=&quot;1060&quot;&gt;G.I.E.O. Gita&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong data-end=&quot;1106&quot; data-start=&quot;1082&quot;&gt;Gita Gyan Sansthanam&lt;/strong&gt;, Kurukshetra.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1209&quot; data-start=&quot;1125&quot;&gt;
		&lt;p data-end=&quot;1209&quot; data-start=&quot;1127&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;1149&quot; data-start=&quot;1127&quot;&gt;Dr. Sonal Mansingh&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong data-end=&quot;1178&quot; data-start=&quot;1151&quot;&gt;Padma Vibhushan awardee&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong data-end=&quot;1208&quot; data-start=&quot;1183&quot;&gt;former Rajya Sabha MP&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Raghuram Rajan Committee&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Raghuram Rajan Committee&lt;/strong&gt; was constituted in 2008 to outline a financial sector reform roadmap, focusing on enhancing access to financial services in India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The committee&amp;#39;s report highlighted the critical need for &lt;strong&gt;financial inclusion&lt;/strong&gt; to improve economic equity and reduce poverty.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It proposed the development of innovative financial instruments and the expansion of banking services, especially in rural and underserved areas.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;One of its significant recommendations included the use of technology and mobile banking to reach the unbanked population.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The committee emphasized the establishment of a competitive financial system that could serve all sections of society efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Inclusion:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Financial inclusion refers to ensuring access to essential financial services, such as savings, credit, and insurance, at affordable costs for all, particularly the disadvantaged and low-income groups.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is considered a key driver for economic growth and poverty alleviation.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Financial inclusion initiatives in India include schemes like &lt;strong&gt;PM Jan Dhan Yojana&lt;/strong&gt; and leveraging technology such as Aadhaar-enabled payment systems.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technology in Financial Inclusion:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Mobile banking, digital wallets, and the use of fintech have revolutionized financial inclusion by making banking accessible even in remote areas.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Technological solutions help reduce transaction costs and improve operational efficiency in financial services.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Committees on Financial Sector Reforms:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Narasimham Committee:&lt;/strong&gt; Focused on banking sector reforms, including asset quality and capital adequacy.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vaghul Committee:&lt;/strong&gt; Addressed money market reforms to improve liquidity and efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Ghosh Committee:&lt;/strong&gt; Examined internal controls and fraud prevention in banks.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pradhan Mantri Jan Dhan Yojana (PMJDY):&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Launched in 2014, this scheme aimed to provide universal access to banking facilities, including zero-balance accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It also promotes financial literacy and direct benefit transfers to beneficiaries.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct Answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IIT Delhi&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
