&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MERCOSUR.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India and Brazil have agreed to expand the scope of their existing Preferential Trade Agreement (PTA) under the MERCOSUR bloc to include more sectors and products.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India signed a Framework Agreement with MERCOSUR in 2003 and a Preferential Trade Agreement (PTA) in 2004, which came into effect in 2009.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The agreement marked India&amp;rsquo;s first formal trade pact with a Latin American bloc, promoting bilateral and inter-regional economic cooperation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The expansion aims to increase trade diversification and include new product categories, strengthening India&amp;ndash;Brazil commercial ties.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MERCOSUR, established in 1991, is one of the largest trading blocs in the world and a key partner in India&amp;rsquo;s South-South trade strategy.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;MERCOSUR (Southern Common Market)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Established: 1991&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Founding Members: Brazil, Argentina, Uruguay, and Paraguay&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Headquarters: Montevideo, Uruguay&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Pending Member: Bolivia (awaiting full ratification)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Associate Members: Chile, Colombia, Ecuador, Guyana, Peru, Suriname, and Panama (first Central American nation to join as associate)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;India&amp;ndash;MERCOSUR Trade Pact&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Framework Agreement signed in 2003&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Preferential Trade Agreement signed in 2004, effective since 2009&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Focuses on reducing tariffs on select products and expanding trade cooperation&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Significance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Encourages South&amp;ndash;South economic collaboration&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Enhances India&amp;rsquo;s access to Latin American markets&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Supports diversification of India&amp;rsquo;s global trade partnerships&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
